cs.DC, cs.CE, cs.SE, cs.DL, cs.DB

This paper discusses the development of a common information model for Grid resources and services, which is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science. The most likely sub-category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as the paper specifically mentions Grid technologies and resource-sharing capabilities over local and wide area networks. Other likely sub-categories include cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) and cs.SE (Software Engineering) as the paper focuses on interoperability among different Grid middleware solutions and the need for a common information model. Additionally, cs.DL (Digital Libraries) and cs.DB (Databases) are also possible sub-categories as the paper discusses resource discovery and monitoring activities.
